Proverbs 21:29 A wicked man hardens his face;
 but as for the upright, he establishes his ways.
Proverbs 21:29 There is no wisdom nor understanding
 nor counsel against Yahweh.
Proverbs 21:29 The horse is prepared for the day of battle;
 but victory is with Yahweh.

Proverbs 22:22-23 Don’t exploit the poor, because he is poor;
 and don’t crush the needy in court;
Proverbs 22:22-23 for Yahweh will plead their case,
 and plunder the life of those who plunder them.

Proverbs 23:26-28 My son, give me your heart;
 and let your eyes keep in my ways.
Proverbs 23:26-28 For a prostitute is a deep pit;
 and a wayward wife is a narrow well.
Proverbs 23:26-28 Yes, she lies in wait like a robber,
 and increases the unfaithful among men.

Proverbs 24:3-4 Through wisdom a house is built;
 by understanding it is established;
Proverbs 24:3-4 by knowledge the rooms are filled
 with all rare and beautiful treasure.

Proverbs 24:5-6 A wise man has great power;
 and a knowledgeable man increases strength;
Proverbs 24:5-6 for by wise guidance you wage your war;
 and victory is in many advisors.

Proverbs 24:15-16 Don’t lay in wait, wicked man, against the habitation of the righteous.
 Don’t destroy his resting place;
Proverbs 24:15-16 for a righteous man falls seven times and rises up again;
 but the wicked are overthrown by calamity.

Proverbs 28:3 A needy man who oppresses the poor
 is like a driving rain which leaves no crops.
Proverbs 28:3 Those who forsake the law praise the wicked;
 but those who keep the law contend with them.
Proverbs 28:3 Evil men don’t understand justice;
 but those who seek Yahweh understand it fully.
Proverbs 28:3 Better is the poor who walks in his integrity,
 than he who is perverse in his ways, and he is rich.
Proverbs 28:3 Whoever keeps the law is a wise son;
 but he who is a companion of gluttons shames his father.
