Proverbs 28:16 Whoever robs his father or his mother and says, “It’s not wrong,”
 is a partner with a destroyer.
Proverbs 28:16 One who is greedy stirs up strife;
 but one who trusts in Yahweh will prosper.
Proverbs 28:16 One who trusts in himself is a fool;
 but one who walks in wisdom is kept safe.
Proverbs 28:16 One who gives to the poor has no lack;
 but one who closes his eyes will have many curses.
Proverbs 28:16 When the wicked rise, men hide themselves;
 but when they perish, the righteous thrive.

Proverbs 28:17 A man who is tormented by life blood will be a fugitive until death;
 no one will support him.
Proverbs 28:17 Whoever walks blamelessly is kept safe;
 but one with perverse ways will fall suddenly.
Proverbs 28:17 One who works his land will have an abundance of food;
 but one who chases fantasies will have his fill of poverty.
Proverbs 28:17 A faithful man is rich with blessings;
 but one who is eager to be rich will not go unpunished.
Proverbs 28:17 To show partiality is not good;
 yet a man will do wrong for a piece of bread.
Proverbs 28:17 A stingy man hurries after riches,
 and doesn’t know that poverty waits for him.
